SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 502
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to recognize Erin Clark on her selection as the
2024–2025 Mt. Juliet Christian Academy
Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Erin Clark is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself as
a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, a Pre-K-3 teacher at Mt. Juliet Christian Academy, Ms. Clark was recently
named the school's 2024–2025 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor for her tenure as an
educator, as it recognizes the positive influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Erin Clark is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who has
worked assiduously throughout her seven-year career in education to motivate her students to
reach their full potential as scholars and citizens; and
WHEREAS, steeped in pedagogical formation, Ms. Clark has earned a degree in
teaching and learning and interdisciplinary studies; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Clark truly serves as an inspiration to the faculty and staff at Mt. Juliet
Christian Academy, and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are
fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Erin Clark epitomizes the dedicated educator who is wholly committed to
the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
